Class TcpDefaultTimeToLive

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.directory.server.dhcp.options.BaseDhcpOption
      • org.apache.directory.server.dhcp.options.DhcpOption
        • org.apache.directory.server.dhcp.options.ByteOption
          • org.apache.directory.server.dhcp.options.tcp.TcpDefaultTimeToLive

  • public class TcpDefaultTimeToLive
extends ByteOption
    This option specifies the default TTL that the client should use when sending TCP segments. The value is represented as an 8-bit unsigned integer. The minimum value is 1. The code for this option is 37, and its length is 1.
